value.string: Rustic Pole home with a detached cottage in a park like setting with lava rock walls. Corner lot in a quiet cull-de-sac, providing a cool, peaceful, and serene refuge. A wrap around deck to enjoy the beautiful mornings and gorgeous sunsets. Ample room for a pool.

Stunning Ocean views from this tree-top Maui Meadows property. Sunsets to dazzle you all year long from the lanai and roof deck. Custom cherry wood (honey-wheat finish) cabinets in kitchen, living, office, bath and laundry. Granite counter-tops in kitchen and bath. Gas cook top with hood that is a 3-in-1 Microwave/Convection/Regular oven. Stainless Steel refrigerator, washer/dryer and ceiling fan in Master are excluded. The driveway easement is shared with neighbors. County records shows this house as a 3bd/3ba.

Diamond in the rough, great potential with ocean view of Molokini. Original owners lived in the home until just recently. Original Owner's Family occupied. Upstairs there are 3 bedrooms, 2 baths spacious living room and large kitchen. Additional unfinished spaces downstairs next to garage, offer areas for further expansion. Office and 1/2 bath located behind garage. 2nd driveway provides access to back of lot with large level area. Ideal area for pool or cottage additions. Backyard also features a tennis court. Call for showings

Wonderful opportunity to own in Maui Meadows! Contractors special on this all original home and cottage with some ocean views. Two story home with detached carport and cottage in rear. Very quiet portion of Maui Meadows with endless possibilities.

Live in and enjoy this property with a lot of matured fruit bearing trees such as Mangoes, Avocados, Coconut, Papayas, and plenty of Banana trees everywhere. Topography is slightly sloped making it very easy to build your main dream home. Produce gives the owner an average of 1,000 to 1,500 dollars income per month at present. This property has 2 water meters - one for the home and one for agriculture.
